begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and then talked about what her job is and what are my hobbies. She said she is a dietician. She asked how many kids I have and what are their ages.
middle_memory_text: We talked about her running a marathon and preparing for one. She talked about what she eats and that she doesn't eat meat anymore and that she's a vegetarian.
end_memory_text: We talked about my kids like to eat and what do I plan to do for the rest of today. We talked about her eating protein and how she helps kids that are picky eaters.
rest_of_day_open: Boring ang long since my husband has to work a lot. I will have to caring for the kids and there are four to look after from the age five and under. I will look forward to the day my husband has off on Thursday. I have to make sure my kids get to school on time.
critical_positive: The other person knew how to have a conversation. She knew that you should introduce yourself first instead of jumping into a conversation. She knew what to talk about and knew how to keep the conversation going when I didn't know what to talk about next. She has experience with conversations.
critical_negative: I didn't know what to talk about and didn't know much about the other person. I didn't know how to start the conversation and continue it. I felt nervous, scared and intimated about the conversation and didn't know to interact. I was the reason things might of got a little awkward if they did.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, my partner and I talked about ourselves and where we are from and what we do for fun, as a job, and in our free time.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, my partner and I talked more about where we live, the season differences of our two states, and food.
end_memory_text: At the end of the conversation, we talked about our food preferences, what we like to eat and cook for meals, and our similar netflix baking show interests.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to go well. I have quite a bit of work to do today and projects to complete but I feel like I have enough time to complete them before the deadline of Friday. I have all of my workouts planned for the week and I am looking forward to completing them.
critical_positive: We were able to find topics that we both had something to say about. Talking about food and our states and weather are easy surface-level topics that we both can have a natural conversation around. We both were able to laugh at the same show that we both watch and I think that was possibly the highlight of the conversation.
critical_negative: I felt like my conversation partner was shy and didn't want to talk to me as much as I was talking to her, but eventually she warmed up a little bit. I don't think I would be friends with this person in real life because she is not as ambitious or outgoing as I am.
